HEADWORD: Favorless
<hw>Fa"vor*less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Unfavored; not
regarded with favor; having no countenance or support.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unpropitious; unfavorable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
